cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Securing Agentic Architectures: A Deliberately Vulnerable Multi-Agent LLM Testbed"
abstract: >-
  Experimental prototype accompanying the master's thesis "Securing Agentic
  Architectures" (TU Wien). A deliberately vulnerable three-agent LLM system
  with seven attack scenarios (memory poisoning, indirect injection, cross-agent
  propagation, planner hijacking, system prompt extraction, memory membership
  probing, and tool result poisoning) and four defences (canary tokens, intent
  anchoring, counterfactual plan diffing, and output spotlighting), evaluated
  across twelve models (four paid API models and eight free local open-weight
  models).
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Bajnok
    given-names: "Dénes Ágoston"
    affiliation: "TU Wien"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-06-30"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/dbajnok99/MasterThesis"
url: "https://github.com/dbajnok99/MasterThesis"
keywords:
  - LLM
  - multi-agent systems
  - agent security
  - prompt injection
  - indirect prompt injection
  - memory poisoning
  - data exfiltration
  - defense evaluation
